    "z05_overview": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "settings": {
        "section_visibility": "always",
        "custom_liquid": "<div class=\"z05-feature-shell\"><section class=\"z05-section z05-overview-section\"><div class=\"z05-wrap\"><div class=\"z05-overview-head\"><div><p class=\"z05-kicker\">Overview</p><h2>A compact hybrid for people who rotate music</h2></div><p>Some IEMs are tuned for one perfect demo track. Z05 AuAg is built for the way most of us listen: albums, playlists, dongles, DAPs, desk chains, and a mood that changes by the hour.</p></div><div class=\"z05-overview-main\"><article><span>01</span><h3>What it is</h3><p>A compact universal hybrid you can live with daily: easy to carry, easy to drive, and serious enough for focused listening.</p></article><article><span>02</span><h3>Why AuAg</h3><p>The gold/silver finish gives the launch pair a bit of ceremony without turning it into a display-only object.</p></article><article><span>03</span><h3>What you get</h3><p>A monitor, cable, 3.5mm, 4.4mm balanced, and Type-C terminations, a carry case, and LiquidMorph tips, all ready to go.</p></article></div><div class=\"z05-overview-summary\"><div><h3>For the listener who changes albums before they change gear</h3><p>Run it from a phone dongle on the way out, then plug into a balanced player or desktop chain at home. The point is simple: keep the Z05 character with fewer little compromises.</p></div><div class=\"z05-overview-specs\" aria-label=\"Z05 AuAg overview specifications\"><article><span>Fit</span><p>No custom mold needed with LiquidMorph tips for a seal you can repeat.</p></article><article><span>Driver platform</span><p>Dynamic-driver body with armature speed and air layered on top.</p></article><article><span>Source path</span><p>3.5mm, 4.4mm balanced, and Type-C terminations in the box.</p></article><article><span>Finish</span><p>Forged-carbon faceplates with Au/Ag foil; 3D-printed shells finished by hand with matching foil lacing.</p></article></div></div></div></section></div><style>.z05-overview-section{background:#f4f1ea;color:#111}.z05-overview-head{display:grid;grid-template-columns:minmax(0,1fr) minmax(360px,.9fr);gap:46px;align-items:end}.z05-overview-head h2{max-width:780px}.z05-overview-head>p{margin:0;color:#28241f;font-size:18px;line-height:1.58}.z05-overview-main{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:18px;margin-top:42px}.z05-overview-main article{border-top:2px solid #111;padding:18px 0 0}.z05-overview-main span{display:block;color:#a87725;font-size:38px;font-weight:900;line-height:1}.z05-overview-main h3{margin:14px 0 10px;color:#111;font-size:20px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0}.z05-overview-main p{margin:0;color:#302b25;font-size:15px;line-height:1.58}.z05-overview-summary{display:grid;grid-template-columns:minmax(320px,.78fr) minmax(0,1.22fr);gap:28px;align-items:start;margin-top:42px;padding-top:30px;border-top:1px solid #cfc8bb}.z05-overview-summary h3{margin:0 0 12px;color:#111;font-size:28px;line-height:1.08;text-transform:uppercase}.z05-overview-summary p{margin:0;color:#302b25;font-size:16px;line-height:1.6}.z05-overview-specs{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,minmax(0,1fr));gap:1px;background:#d8d0c3;border:1px solid #d8d0c3}.z05-overview-specs article{background:#fff;padding:20px;min-width:0}.z05-overview-specs span{display:block;margin-bottom:10px;color:#6d4b16;font-size:11px;font-weight:900;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.08em}.z05-overview-specs p{margin:0;color:#302b25;font-size:14px;line-height:1.52;overflow-wrap:anywhere}@media(max-width:980px){.z05-overview-head,.z05-overview-summary{grid-template-columns:1fr}.z05-overview-main{grid-template-columns:1fr}.z05-overview-head{gap:20px}.z05-overview-main{margin-top:30px}}@media(max-width:640px){.z05-overview-specs{grid-template-columns:1fr}.z05-overview-head>p{font-size:16px}.z05-overview-main span{font-size:34px}.z05-overview-summary h3{font-size:23px}}</style>",
