    "z05_engineering": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "settings": {
        "section_visibility": "always",
        "custom_liquid": "<div id=\"z05-engineering\" class=\"z05-feature-shell\"><section class=\"z05-section dark z05-engineering-section\"><div class=\"z05-wrap\"><div class=\"z05-engineering-head\"><div><p class=\"z05-kicker\">Craft & Sound</p><h2>Made to be worn, then looked at twice</h2></div><div class=\"z05-engineering-copy\"><p>The shell has to disappear before the finish gets to show off. Z05 AuAg starts with a compact universal fit, repeatable seal, and a driver layout that can stay convincing across long sessions.</p><p>The forged-carbon look is on the faceplates. The body is a 3D-printed shell, then each pair is dressed by hand with gold and silver foil work. It takes hours because the finish has to feel intentional, not sprinkled on.</p></div></div><div class=\"z05-craft-strip\" aria-label=\"Z05 AuAg craft notes\"><article><span>Faceplate</span><b>Forged carbon with Au/Ag foil</b></article><article><span>Shell body</span><b>3D-printed universal monitor shell</b></article><article><span>Finish time</span><b>Hand-laced over hours per pair</b></article></div><div class=\"z05-engineering-body\"><div class=\"z05-build-card z05-engineering-specs\"><strong>AAW Z05 AuAg</strong><dl><dt>Format</dt><dd>Universal-fit hybrid in-ear monitor</dd><dt>Low End</dt><dd>10mm PET diaphragm dynamic woofer</dd><dt>Clarity</dt><dd>Mid and super-high BA drivers for vocal edge and air</dd><dt>Voice Control</dt><dd>TwinCore physical voicing switch</dd><dt>Pressure Flow</dt><dd>Bass-Flow vent pressure system</dd><dt>Finish</dt><dd>Forged-carbon faceplates; 3D-printed shells with hand-laced gold and silver foil finish</dd><dt>In The Box</dt><dd>2-pin detachable cable, 3.5mm, 4.4mm balanced, Type-C terminations, carrying case, LiquidMorph eartips</dd></dl></div><figure class=\"z05-engineering-hero\"><img src=\"{{ 'z05-auag-luxury-shell-geometry.jpg' | asset_url }}\" alt=\"Z05 AuAg shells in a minimalist luxury studio setting\" loading=\"lazy\"><figcaption><b>Shell form, finish, and fit</b><span>The finish catches the eye; the compact shell shape is what lets you keep listening.</span></figcaption></figure></div></div></section></div><style>.z05-engineering-section{background:#070707}.z05-engineering-head{display:grid;grid-template-columns:minmax(360px,.92fr) minmax(420px,1.08fr);gap:54px;align-items:end}.z05-engineering-head h2{max-width:760px}.z05-engineering-copy{display:grid;gap:14px}.z05-engineering-copy p{margin:0;color:#d8d1c7;font-size:17px;line-height:1.62}.z05-craft-strip{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1px;margin:34px 0 0;background:rgba(255,255,255,.14);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.14)}.z05-craft-strip article{background:#111;padding:20px 22px;min-height:104px}.z05-craft-strip span{display:block;margin-bottom:10px;color:#e2b768;font-size:12px;font-weight:900;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.08em}.z05-craft-strip b{display:block;color:#fff;font-size:19px;line-height:1.22}.z05-engineering-body{display:grid;grid-template-columns:minmax(340px,.82fr) minmax(0,1.18fr);gap:24px;align-items:stretch;margin-top:24px}.z05-engineering-specs{padding:28px}.z05-engineering-specs dl{grid-template-columns:128px 1fr}.z05-engineering-hero{margin:0;position:relative;overflow:hidden;min-height:460px;background:#111;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.12)}.z05-engineering-hero img{display:block;width:100%;height:100%;min-height:460px;aspect-ratio:16/10;object-fit:cover}.z05-engineering-hero figcaption{position:absolute;left:50%;right:auto;bottom:14px;width:min(520px,calc(100% - 28px));transform:translateX(-50%);background:rgba(0,0,0,.72);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.14);padding:13px;color:#f2e5c5;text-align:center}.z05-engineering-hero b{display:block;font-size:12px;line-height:1.15;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.06em}.z05-engineering-hero span{display:block;margin-top:7px;color:#d6cec2;font-size:12px;line-height:1.38}@media(max-width:980px){.z05-engineering-head,.z05-engineering-body{grid-template-colu